 Princess cruise ship: estimating the epidemic potential and effectiveness of public health countermeasures | journal = Journal of Travel Medicine | date = February 2020 | pmid = 32109273 | doi = 10.1093/jtm/taaa030 | pmc = 7107563 |name-list-format = vanc}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"QZ-Why\">{{Cite news|url=https://qz.com/1820422/coronavirus-why-wont-who-use-the-name-sars-cov-2/|title=Why won't the WHO call the coronavirus by its name, SARS-CoV-2?|vauthors=Hui M|work=[[Quartz (publication)|Quartz]]|date=18 March 2020|access-date=26 March 2020|name-list-format=vanc|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200325235531/https://qz.com/1820422/coronavirus-why-wont-who-use-the-name-sars-cov-2/|archive-date=25 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"ScienceFlawed\">{{cite journal |title=Study claiming new coronavirus can be transmitted by people without symptoms was flawed |journal=[[Science (journal)|Science]] |vauthors=Kupferschmidt K|date=February 2020 | doi=10.1126/science.abb1524 |name-list-format = vanc}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"ScienceRapid\">{{cite journal |vauthors=Li R, Pei S, Chen B, Song Y, Zhang T, Yang W, Shaman J |title=Substantial undocumented infection facilitates the rapid dissemination of novel coronavirus (SARS-CoV2) |journal=[[Science (journal)|Science]] |pages=eabb3221 |date=16 March 2020 |access-date=17 March 2020 |display-authors = 6 |doi=10.1126/science.abb3221 |pmid=32179701 |url=https://science.sciencemag.org/content/early/2020/03/13/science.abb3221 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200317000008/https://science.sciencemag.org/content/early/2020/03/13/science.abb3221 |archive-date=17 March 2020 |url-status=live |name-list-format = vanc}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"SCI-20200219\">{{cite journal | vauthors = Wrapp D, Wang N, Corbett KS, Goldsmith JA, Hsieh CL, Abiona O, Graham BS, McLellan JS | display-authors = 6 | title = Cryo-EM structure of the 2019-nCoV spike in the prefusion conformation | journal = [[Science (journal)|Science]] | vol